Specify the Database Path.

Database Path is the top directory of the created database 
where all files are stored by default. 
The DB description file 'tbdesc' is always stored within this 
directory, all other files and subdirectories can also be placed 
elsewhere.
The default for the Database Directory is './dbname@machine'

   -	This DB parameter cannot be changed after DB creation.

   -	Command Line Syntax :   h=<path>
